@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam boxPadding 8
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderThickness 2
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFDD
skinparam ParticipantBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam SequenceMessageAlignment left

title RIMA PoC - Content Catalog Build Flow\nTask 644 / June 2026

participant "MapComponent" as mapComp #E8F5E9
participant "CatalogService" as catalogSvc #F3E5F5
participant "CatalogStore\n[SignalStore]" as catalogStore #F3E5F5
participant "WebmapService" as webmapSvc #F3E5F5
participant "LanguageStore\n[SignalStore]" as langStore #FFF8E7
participant "language-info-config" as langConfig #FFF8E7
participant "PortalService" as portalSvc #F3E5F5
participant "ArcGIS Portal" as portal #FFEBEE
participant "LayerService" as layerSvc #E8F5E9

== Catalog Build Entry Point ==

mapComp -> catalogSvc : [ASYNC] buildMapCatalog()
activate catalogSvc
catalogSvc -> catalogStore : setLoadState('loading')

== Step 1 - Acquire WebmapCollection ==

catalogSvc -> webmapSvc : [ASYNC] getWebmapCollection()
activate webmapSvc

note over webmapSvc
  Cache check:
  1. webmapCollection signal != undefined? -> return cached
  2. loadPromise != undefined? -> return in-flight promise
  3. Otherwise: start fresh load
end note

webmapSvc -> langStore : read activeLanguage()\n-> 'de'
webmapSvc -> langConfig : lookup catalogId for 'de'\n-> 'DE Sample'

note over langConfig
  Language-to-Portal category mapping:
  de -> 'DE'
  fr -> 'FR'
  it -> 'IT'
  Source: src/i18n/language-info-config.ts
end note

webmapSvc -> portalSvc : [ASYNC] queryItems(\n  categories: ['/Categories/DE'],\n  query: 'type:"Web Map"',\n  num: 100, sortField: 'title')
activate portalSvc
portalSvc -> portal : [ASYNC] Portal.load() + portal.queryItems()
activate portal
portal --> portalSvc : PortalItem[]
deactivate portal
portalSvc --> webmapSvc : PortalItem[]
deactivate portalSvc

note over webmapSvc
  Promise.all() - load all WebMaps in parallel
end note

group Parallel: for each PortalItem
  webmapSvc -> portal : [ASYNC] new WebMap({ portalItem }).load()
  activate portal
  portal --> webmapSvc : WebMap (loaded)
  deactivate portal

  webmapSvc -> webmapSvc : transformWebMapLayers(webMap.layers)\n\nFor each ArcGIS SDK layer:\n  - GroupLayer -> WebmapGroupLayer (recurse children)\n  - FeatureLayer -> WebmapFeatureLayer\n  - MapImageLayer -> WebmapMapServiceLayer\n  - WMTSLayer -> WebmapWebTiledLayer\n\nFilter: only INCLUDED_LAYER_TYPES\n  ['ArcGISFeatureLayer', 'WebTiledLayer']\n\nSkip layers with unsupported type
  webmapSvc -> webmapSvc : extractCategorySegments(item.categories)\n-> split path, skip 'Categories' + language root\n-> e.g. ['Roads', 'National']
end group

webmapSvc -> webmapSvc : Build WebmapCollection {\n  loadState: 'loaded',\n  webmaps: WebmapData[]\n}\nStore in signal cache
webmapSvc --> catalogSvc : WebmapCollection
deactivate webmapSvc

== Step 2 - Collect Leaf Entries ==

catalogSvc -> catalogSvc : collectLeafEntries(webmapCollection)\n\n1. Sort webmaps by categorySegments + title\n2. For each webmap:\n   a. Build basePath from category segments\n      [{ id:'category:Roads', origin:'category' },\n       { id:'category:National', origin:'category' }]\n   b. (Optional) append webmap title as segment\n      [disabled: WEBMAP_NAME_AS_SECTION = false]\n   c. Recurse into layers:

note over catalogSvc
  collectLayerEntries() recursion:

  - GroupLayer:
      append path segment { origin:'group-layer' }
      recurse into child layers

  - ArcGISFeatureLayer:
      create CatalogFeatureLayer leaf
      push { path, leaf } to entries

  - ArcGISMapServiceLayer:
      create CatalogMapImageLayer leaf
      push { path, leaf } to entries

  - WebTiledLayer:
      create CatalogWebTiledLayer leaf
      push { path, leaf } to entries

  Result: flat array of CatalogLeafEntry[]
  Each entry = { path: CatalogPathSegment[], leaf: CatalogLayer }
end note

== Step 3 - Tree Assembly ==

catalogSvc -> catalogSvc : depositAtPath() for each entry\n\nWalk path segments:\n  1. Find or create CatalogSection at current level\n     (matched by id)\n  2. Descend into section.items\n  3. Repeat until path exhausted\n  4. Push leaf into deepest section.items

note over catalogSvc
  Example resulting tree:

  Catalog.items = [
    CatalogSection { title:'Roads', origin:'category', items:[
      CatalogSection { title:'National', origin:'category', items:[
        CatalogSection { title:'Group A', origin:'group-layer', items:[
          CatalogFeatureLayer { title:'Bridges', url:... }
          CatalogWebTiledLayer { title:'Aerial', url:... }
        ]}
      ]}
    ]}
  ]

  Multiple webmaps sharing the same category path
  merge their layers into the same section nodes.
end note

== Step 4 - Store and Return ==

catalogSvc -> catalogStore : setCatalog(catalog)\n-> patchState({ catalog, loadState:'loaded' })
catalogSvc --> mapComp : Catalog
deactivate catalogSvc

== Layer Rendering ==

mapComp -> layerSvc : [SYNC] addCatalogToMap(catalog)
activate layerSvc

layerSvc -> layerSvc : buildLayersFromItems(catalog.items)\n\nRecursive mapping:\n  CatalogSection -> GroupLayer { title, layers:[] }\n  CatalogFeatureLayer -> FeatureLayer { url }\n  CatalogMapImageLayer -> MapImageLayer { url }\n  CatalogWebTiledLayer -> WMTSLayer { url, activeLayer }\n  CatalogDocument -> skipped\n\nlayers.reverse() (z-order correction)

layerSvc -> mapComp : view.map.addMany(arcgisLayers)
deactivate layerSvc

note over mapComp
  Catalog tree is now mirrored as ArcGIS SDK layers on the map.
  The arcgis-layer-list (ToC) reads the map layer collection
  and reflects the same hierarchy to the user.
end note

@enduml
